messages.content:
I've updated the CSS file to prevent the link underlining on hover for the cards while maintaining the same visual appearance. The changes I made:

1. Added a specific rule for links within the `.cards` container to ensure no text decoration on hover:
   ```css
   .cards a {
       text-decoration: none;
   }

   .cards a:hover {
       text-decoration: none;
   }
   ```

2. Kept the original hover underline effect for regular links elsewhere in the document (like in the "All Posts" list) to maintain consistency with typical web conventions.

The cursor will still change to a pointer when hovering over the cards since that's the default behavior for anchor tags, but the text won't be underlined on hover, giving you the clean look you wanted for the cards while preserving the usual link behavior for regular text links.

args.content:
body {
    font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    background-color: #f4f4f4;
}

header {
    background-color: #333;
    color: #fff;
    padding: 10px 0;
    text-align: center;
}

header h1 {
    margin: 0;
    color: #fff; /* Ensure the header text is white */
}

header h1 a {
    color: #fff; /* Ensure the header link text is white */
    text-decoration: none;
}

main {
    padding: 20px;
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 20px auto;
    background-color: #fff;
    border-radius: 5px;
    box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
}

.cards {
    display: flex;
    gap: 20px;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
}

.card {
    flex: 1;
    padding: 15px;
    border: 1px solid #ddd;
    border-radius: 5px;
    background-color: #f9f9f9;
    transition: transform 0.3s ease, box-shadow 0.3s ease;
}

.card h3 {
    margin-top: 0;
}

.card a {
    text-decoration: none;
    color: #333;
}

/* Remove the hover underline for card links */
.cards a {
    text-decoration: none;
}

.cards a:hover {
    text-decoration: none;
}

/* Add shadow and float effect on hover */
.cards a:hover .card {
    transform: translateY(-5px);
    box-shadow: 0 5px 15px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2);
}

/* But we'll keep the hover effect for regular links in the article */
article {
    margin-bottom: 20px;
}

h1, h2 {
    color: #333;
}

ul {
    list-style-type: none;
    padding: 0;
}

li {
    margin-bottom: 10px;
}

a {
    color: #333;
    text-decoration: none;
}

a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
}

footer {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 10px 0;
    background-color: #333;
    color: #fff;
    position: fixed;
    width: 100%;
    bottom: 0;
}
